overview: The user initiated a task to review and enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application. The agent performed a thorough analysis of the existing codebase
  against the provided Statement of Work and a detailed questionnaire
  specification, identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent
  systematically addressed these gaps by implementing a new 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores. It also added
  sophisticated detection logic for complex sleep disorders like COMISA
  (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Further
  enhancements included integrating placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep
  and mental health resources within the report, implementing a weighted scoring
  system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS), and expanding the CSV export
  functionality to capture all questionnaire data. Additionally, the agent
  introduced new questions for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening. The
  agent was working on adding medical and mental health history sections when
  the conversation ended.
